# Lab 06 – DNS Reconnaissance with nslookup, dig, and whois 

## Objective

In the previous five labs, I was looking at devices on my own local
network. I was finding machines, knocking on ports, and identifying
services. Everything was close — machines I could touch, on a network
I controlled.

This lab went somewhere different. Instead of looking inward at my
own network, I started looking outward — at the internet itself. I
wanted to understand how names like google.com connect to actual
addresses, who owns those names, and what anyone can find out just
by asking the right questions.

The tools in this lab do not scan anything. They ask questions and
listen to the answers.

