## What the Two Machines Showed Together

Running everything on both Kali and Linux Mint and comparing the results
was more useful than running on one machine alone.

The DNS server addresses looked different — Kali used the gateway,
Mint used its local resolver. But every answer they came back with was
identical. Same IP addresses. Same mail server. Same whois data.

That consistency is what a healthy network looks like. If the two
machines had returned different addresses for the same domain, that
would have been the first sign that something was wrong.

