## How This Connects to the Previous Labs

The first five labs looked at what was happening on the local network —
which machines were alive, which ports were open, which services were
running. All of that was close and visible.

This lab looked further out. DNS sits between every device and the
internet. Understanding it is understanding how traffic finds its way
anywhere at all. The port 53 that appeared in DNS queries here is the
same port 53 that would show up if a DNS service were running on a
local machine being scanned. Everything connects.

